&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the busy Outpatients Appointment Centre. The Outpatient Appointment Centre (OAC) is the start of 18-week Referral to Treatment (RTT) Pathway for Patients. The OAC manages multiple specialities requiring candidates to possess an ability to learn quickly, retain large amounts of information and enjoy working in a pressured environment where targets need to be delivered within an agreed time-frame. The post holder will use the Patient Administration System (PAS) and NHS eReferral Service and telephone queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of any secondary care provider PAS system, Call centre or similar experience of attending to high volume complex telephone queries is essential. Excellent IT skills and working on MS office and computer applications/systems are also an essential requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for ensuring that Trust’s Patient Access Policy, CARES standards and data quality standards are adhered to and promote good practice at all times with system users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
